OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FLargely cloudy at first today,
OL,6,Fbut some brighter spells will develop
OL,7,Fat times. A few spots of rain are
OL,8,Fpossible where the cloud thickens.
OL,9,FBreezy, but feeling pleasant in the
OL,10,Fsunshine.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FShowers easing away for a
OL,13,Ftime, but further outbreaks of rain
OL,14,Farriving after midnight. A mild night
OL,15,Funder the blanket of cloud.
OL,16,
OL,17,CThursday:FA grey and wet start to the
OL,18,Fday across Wales. However, rain will
OL,19,Fgradually ease, with some drier and
OL,20,Fpossible brighter warm spells in the
OL,21,Fafternoon.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
